        "timestamp": "2020-04-01 07:14:42.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\n> Patch Set 1: Code-Review+1\n> \n> I am not sure to get the full picture, I planned a slot this afternnon to have a better understanding.\n> the goal is to replace what we have in csit today?\n\nThis is not replacing anything - it's additional layer of verification tests. In integration repos we have several projects based on docker-compose and currently they're not verified (except with linter job) at application level, i.e. no job to verify the docker-compose.yml is valid and still usable by docker-compose do launch services. No csit tests will be run in created containers, just the containers/services themselves to verify docker-compose setup.",
